    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.11ga"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">11h</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    Skeffington &amp; Son, Ltd.
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">PUBLISHERS &amp; EXPORTERS
                
                LONDON ∙ NEW YORK ∙ MELBOURNE ∙ SYDNEY ∙ CAPE TOWN
                
                EDITORIAL: MAYFAIR 9801
                TRADE DEPT. PHONE CITY 7251  ACCOUNTS: KEN 9211
                TELEGRAMS AND CABLES: LITERARIUS MAYFAIR LONDON
                CHAIRMAN
                M.D. HUTCHINSON
                DIRECTOR
                K.H. WEBB
                
                HUTCHINSON HOUSE
                STRATFORD PLACE,
                W.1
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <salute>My dear Professor Neihardt-</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have pleasure in sending you the first set of Galley-ships (No's 1-21 inc.) for your "<hi rend="underline">Eagle Voice</hi>". And I should be greatly obliged <hi rend="underline">if you would return them as quickly as possible</hi>. Please keep <hi rend="underline">all</hi> corrections <unclear>down</unclear> to the absolute minimum. And please remember that there will be some very slight variation between these Galleys + your original American edition. This will arise where I may have <hi rend="underline">cut out</hi> a purely American word, or where I have "anglicised" an American word.</p>
                
                <p>Your last letter touched me very 
                
                <hi rend="caps">WHILE GREAT CARE IS TAKEN OF ALL MSS RECEIVED, MESSRS SKEFFINGTON &amp; SON, LTD., CANNOT ACCEPT ANY RESPONSIBILITY OR LIABILITY IN CASE OF LOSS OR DAMAGE</hi>
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.11h-11k_0001"/>
                
                    <fw type="curatorial">11i</fw>
                
                    <fw type="authorial">2</fw>
                
                    very deeply. I feel as though we had known each other all our lives: but then (as you know) physical proximity has little to do with truly "knowing" a person. One day I hope we meet. There is one thing I would ask you &#8212; have you any Indian relic you might give me? I am particularly in love with <hi rend="underline">stones</hi> by that I don't mean opals, diamond, rubies or garnets! There is a great affinity between <hi rend="underline">stones</hi> + myself. When I ask for a relic I don't of course, mean the kind of thing the tourist collects. A polished bone, a magic stone, a piece of sacred <unclear>word</unclear>. These are the things I have in mind. All my life the Red man has drawn me, yet I have never <del><unclear>been</unclear></del> been in his land + have no
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.11h-11k_0002"/>
                
                    <fw type="curatorial">11j</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    Skeffington &amp; Son, Ltd.
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">PUBLISHERS &amp; EXPORTERS
                
                LONDON ∙ NEW YORK ∙ MELBOURNE ∙ SYDNEY ∙ CAPE TOWN
                
                EDITORIAL: MAYFAIR 9801
                TRADE DEPT. PHONE CITY 7251  ACCOUNTS: KEN 9211
                TELEGRAMS AND CABLES: LITERARIUS MAYFAIR LONDON
                CHAIRMAN
                M.D. HUTCHINSON
                DIRECTOR
                K.H. WEBB
                
                HUTCHINSON HOUSE
                STRATFORD PLACE,
                W.1
                </fw>
                
                    <fw type="authorial">3</fw>
                
                    tangible contact with him. This I would appreciate very much. Round my neck I carry (on a silver chain) a piece of sacred jade given to me nearly 35 years ago by an ancient chinaman who befriended me when I was a starving youngster in Liverpool. This is the kind of thing I would love from your hands.</p>
                
                <p>I am making enquiries<sic>inquiries</sic> for you about- the idea of a lecture tour. But I can tell you now that we are not "lecture-tour-conscious" as Americans are. (Though this I'm sure you know).
                
                <hi rend="caps">WHILE GREAT CARE IS TAKEN OF ALL MSS RECEIVED, MESSRS SKEFFINGTON &amp; SON, LTD., CANNOT ACCEPT ANY RESPONSIBILITY OR LIABILITY IN CASE OF LOSS OR DAMAGE</hi>
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.11h-11k_0003"/>
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">11k</fw>
                
                    <fw type="authorial">4</fw>
                    
                    However I have contacts in some of the universities.....<unclear>+ I</unclear> shall continue my enquiries<sic>inquiries</sic>. I hope its possible to  fix something up.</p>
                
                <p>God bless + keep you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very sincerely</salute>
                James Whittaker
                Manager
                11th Dec 1952
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Professor John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route 6.</addrLine>
                        <hi rend="underline">Columbia, Mo. <hi rend="caps">U.S.A.</hi></hi></addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
